courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:   
• Have an in-depth knowledge in scientific method and research management;    
• Develop competencies in finding, reading and critically evaluating relevant scientific literature;    
• Acquire skills in information searching, scientific writing and oral communication;    
• Master generic skills such as critical thinking, team building and lifelong learning techniques;    
• Understand the basic statistical concepts and perform statistical analysis of biological data;    
• Learn the importance of academic honesty.

Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:   
• Have in-depth knowledge and skills in scientific method and research process;    
• Develop competencies in finding, reading and critically evaluating relevant scientific literature;    
• Execute experiments and analyze data carefully;    
• Perform statistical analysis of data with good interpretation and discussion;    
• Master generic skills such as critical thinking, team building and lifelong learning techniques;    
• Understand the importance of academic honesty.
